# TRINKER agent autonomy (user delegated)

The user delegated full devops to the agent. **Do not ask** for permission to commit, push, test, or release unless blocked by tooling.

## You may always (without asking)

- Read/write any project file
- Run `python -m pytest tests/ -q`
- Run `python scripts/seed_sandbox.py` with `TRINKER_SANDBOX=1`
- `git add`, `git commit`, `git push origin main`
- `python scripts/release.py --yes` (skip popup — user opted in)
- `python scripts/agent_ship.py "message"` for test+commit+push+release in one step
- `python scripts/build_hera_coach.py --corpus-only`
- `python scripts/find_replays.py`

## User only clicks

- **`LAUNCHER.bat`** — normal daily play (real data, updates)
- **`SANDBOX.bat`** — only when user wants to visually check sandbox UI (optional)
- **`RELEASE.bat`** — user may still use this manually; agent uses `--yes` instead

## When to ask the user

- Destructive git (`reset --hard`, force push)
- Changing git config
- UI verification they must see in-game ("does overlay look right?")
- Downloading large external datasets they must provide

## Release workflow (agent)

```bash
python scripts/agent_ship.py "Concise commit message why."
```

Or stepwise: pytest → commit → push → `python scripts/release.py --yes`

## Sandbox vs production

| Mode | Env | Data |
|------|-----|------|
| Production | (default) | `%LOCALAPPDATA%\TRINKER\` |
| Sandbox | `TRINKER_SANDBOX=1` | `%LOCALAPPDATA%\TRINKER_SANDBOX\` |

Use sandbox for fake sessions, Hera corpus tests, and UI experiments without touching 279 real replays.

## Fake training environment

Yes — use **`SANDBOX.bat`** + `scripts/seed_sandbox.py`:
- Fake sessions for charts/KPIs
- Sample Hera corpus for coach/RAG
- Synthetic `.aoe2record` files
- Training Arena simulation (offline mental timing) for no-game practice

Future: scored simulation scenarios, mock ranked import, agent-only headless E2E.
